# Cursor Knowledge Sources for SS13/BYOND Development

## Essential Sources (Highest Priority)

### BYOND/DM Language and Runtime
- **BYOND Dream Maker Language Reference**: https://www.byond.com/docs/ref/
  - Priority: CRITICAL
  - Purpose: Core language syntax, procs, types, datums, signals, spawn, sleep, qdel, GC chains
  - Notes: Essential for all DM development

- **BYOND Reference/Guide**: https://www.byond.com/docs/guide/
  - Priority: CRITICAL
  - Purpose: Standard procs, types, datums, signals, spawn, sleep, qdel, GC-цепочки
  - Notes: Core runtime documentation

- **BYOND 515/516 Release Notes**: https://www.byond.com/forum/post/2871235
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Purpose: Changes in procs, lists, path operations, compiler warnings for 515→516 migration
  - Notes: Important for version compatibility

### /tg/station Base Codebase
- **/tg/station Repository**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation
  - Priority: CRITICAL
  - Purpose: Complete codebase + /docs/ (subsystem codes, controller/SS guide, process queues, timers, tick director)
  - Notes: Base fork reference

- **/tg/station Documentation**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/tree/master/docs
  - Priority: CRITICAL
  - Purpose: Subsystem documentation, architecture guides, coding standards
  - Notes: Essential for understanding core systems

- **CONTRIBUTING / Coding Standards**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Purpose: Variable/path naming, macros, patterns (Signals, Components, Elements, Initialize/Destroy)
  - Notes: Style guide and conventions

### Mapping and Tools
- **Mapping & mapmerge2 Guide**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/docs/Mapping.md
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Purpose: How to edit .dmm files, map rules, running mapmerge2
  - Notes: Essential for map development

- **Unit Tests (DMUnit)**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/docs/UnitTests.md
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: Test structure, writing logic checks
  - Notes: Quality assurance

- **CI Guide**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/docs/CICD.md
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: MapDiffBot, linters, avoiding broken diffs
  - Notes: Prevents CI issues

### TGUI Frontend
- **TGUI Documentation**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/tgui/README.md
  - Priority: CRITICAL
  - Purpose: Architecture, signals, useBackend, act(), messages, localization, state, hot reload
  - Notes: Essential for UI development

- **TGUI Component Reference**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/tgui/docs/component-reference.md
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Purpose: Button, Section, Stack, Tabs, Tooltip, NumberInput, LabeledList components
  - Notes: UI building blocks

- **TGUI Style/UX Guide**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/tgui/docs/style-guide.md
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: Spacing, font sizes, grids, contrasts, accessibility
  - Notes: UI/UX best practices

## Important Environment and Toolchain

### Development Tools
- **SpacemanDMM / dmdoc / DreamChecker**: https://github.com/SpaceManiac/SpacemanDMM
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Purpose: Static analysis, doc generation, GC problem highlighting
  - Notes: Code quality tools

- **StrongDMM**: https://github.com/SpaiR/StrongDMM
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: Opening/validating maps
  - Notes: Map development tool

- **mapmerge2 Documentation**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/tools/mapmerge2/README.md
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Purpose: Pre-commit rules
  - Notes: Map merging tool

- **RustG**: https://github.com/tgstation/rust-g
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: Installation, building, versions (if used)
  - Notes: Performance optimization

### Configuration and Deployment
- **Game Configuration**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/config/example/config.txt
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: game_options.txt values, flags, subsystem configs, feature flags
  - Notes: Server configuration

- **Admin/Permissions**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/config/admin_ranks.txt
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: Ranks, flags, safe verbs, logging
  - Notes: Administration system

- **Server Setup**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/docs/installation.md
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: Local server, tick/subsystem profiling
  - Notes: Development environment

## Domain Knowledge SS13

### Game Design and Mechanics
- **Subsystem Documentation**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/docs/Subsystems.md
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Purpose: Air, atmos, power, processing; queues and priorities
  - Notes: Core game systems

- **Component/Element Documentation**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/docs/Components.md
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Purpose: Component pattern, Element pattern
  - Notes: Code architecture

- **Projectile/Signal Systems**: https://github.com/tgstation/tgstation/blob/master/docs/Projectiles.md
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: How shooting, damage, status effects are implemented
  - Notes: Combat systems

### Project-Specific Knowledge
- **Shiptest Wiki**: https://wiki.celadon.pro/
  - Priority: HIGH
  - Purpose: Gameplay wiki for your fork (roles, UI flows, access, recipes)
  - Notes: Understanding how things should work from player perspective

- **Space Systems/Shuttles**: Internal design docs (if available)
  - Priority: MEDIUM
  - Purpose: Thrust physics, visibility radii, autopilot, weapons
  - Notes: Space-specific mechanics

## Asset Guidelines

### Visual and Audio Assets
